CatDescriptText: Theodore Ketchum, tailor, 507 Erin St., was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 29, 1959, pg. A1 with question: Do you believe the state and city FEPC laws are helping Negroes to get jobs they never held before?" answer reads: "I have never heard of any Negroes getting jobs they never held before through the state or FEPC laws."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Theodore Ketchum posed in dry cleaning or tailor shop
